article.headline: Kent State 67, Northern Illinois 57
article.story: KENT, Ohio (AP) -- Kevin Warzynski had 16 points and 10 rebounds, and Kent State got off to a fast start in beating Northern Illinois 67-57 Sunday. The Golden Flashes (15-7, 7-4 Mid-American Conference) took an 11-3 lead in the first five minutes and led by as many as 17 points in the first half, when they shot 58.3 percent from the field. The Huskies (8-12, 4-8) pulled to 42-32 at halftime, but got no closer than nine points in the second half. Northern Illinois' only lead in the game was at 1-0. Nate Gerwig added 14 points for Kent State and Jason Edwin scored 10. Mike McKinney and Paige Paulsen each scored 12 points for Northern Illinois. Kent State tied Akron and Ohio for second place in the MAC East Division, two games behind Miami of Ohio.
